PRIVACY POLICY

Last updated: June 12, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how Couples Dare – Fun Quiz (“the App”, “we”, “our”, or “us”) handles information when you use the App.

Couples Dare – Fun Quiz is a mobile entertainment app for couples. The App includes quiz-style game modes, daily dares, rewards, hearts, badges, streaks, premium mood packs, a daily chemistry board, heart-based activities, and party mode features.

1. DEVELOPER INFORMATION

App name: Couples Dare – Fun Quiz
Package name: com.lauri.couplesdare
Contact email: [flirtyquiz.contact@gmail.com](mailto:flirtyquiz.contact@gmail.com)

2. INFORMATION WE DO NOT REQUIRE

The App does not require users to create an account.

We do not ask users to provide their full name, email address, phone number, home address, contacts, photos, camera access, microphone access, or precise location in order to use the main features of the App.

3. INFORMATION STORED LOCALLY ON YOUR DEVICE

Some information is stored locally on your device to make the App work properly and preserve your game progress. This may include:

* Player names entered by the user, such as Player A and Player B;
* Selected language and theme preferences;
* Music and sound preferences;
* Hearts balance;
* Daily reward status;
* Daily special dare status;
* Daily Chemistry Board progress;
* Couple streak progress;
* Unlocked badges;
* Heart Economy activity usage;
* Party Mode scores and local game progress;
* Premium unlock status.

This information is used to provide app functionality and improve the user experience inside the App. This local information remains on your device unless processed by third-party services described in this Privacy Policy.

4. ADVERTISING

The App uses Google AdMob to display advertisements. These may include banner ads, interstitial ads, and rewarded ads.

Rewarded ads are optional. Users may choose to watch a rewarded ad in order to receive in-app rewards, such as hearts. Rewarded ads are not required to use the basic features of the App.

Google AdMob may collect and process certain information, which may include device identifiers, advertising identifiers, app interactions, approximate location derived from IP address, diagnostic data, crash-related data, and ad performance data.

This data may be used by Google to provide, measure, personalize, and improve advertising, depending on your device settings, consent choices, region, and applicable laws.

You can manage ad personalization through your device settings and Google settings, where available. In certain regions, you may also be shown consent or privacy options related to advertising.

You can learn more about how Google uses information from apps that use Google services here:
https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites

5. FIREBASE ANALYTICS AND CRASH REPORTING

The App may use Firebase services, including Firebase Analytics and Firebase Crashlytics, to understand app usage, improve features, detect errors, and fix crashes.

Firebase may collect information such as app interactions, app launches, device information, operating system information, crash logs, diagnostic data, installation identifiers, and performance-related information.

We use this information to improve stability, fix technical problems, and understand how users interact with the App. We do not use Firebase to identify users by name.

You can learn more about Firebase privacy and security here:
https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy

6. IN-APP PURCHASES AND PREMIUM FEATURES

The App may offer a one-time Premium upgrade through Google Play Billing.

The Premium upgrade may remove ads and unlock premium features such as premium mood packs or other premium experiences.

Purchases are processed by Google Play. We do not collect or store your payment card details.

Payment processing, refunds, purchase validation, and transaction records are handled by Google Play according to Google Play policies.

7. IN-APP HEARTS, REWARDS, BADGES, AND STREAKS

The App includes virtual in-app items and progress features such as hearts, rewards, badges, streaks, Daily Chemistry Board progress, Heart Economy activities, Party Mode progress, and premium activity unlocks.

Hearts and other virtual items have no real-world monetary value, cannot be exchanged for cash, and cannot be transferred outside the App.

8. DATA SHARING

We do not sell your personal information.

Certain information may be processed by third-party service providers used in the App, including:

* Google AdMob, for advertising and rewarded ads;
* Google Firebase, for analytics, diagnostics, and crash reporting;
* Google Play Billing, for in-app purchases.

These third-party providers process data according to their own privacy policies and terms.

9. INTERNET ACCESS

Some features require internet access, including loading ads, rewarded ads, purchase validation, Firebase analytics, crash reporting, and Google Play services.

The App’s core game experience may use local data, but monetization, analytics, crash reporting, and purchase-related features may require connectivity.

10. CHILDREN’S PRIVACY

The App is intended for a general audience and is not directed to children under the age of 13.

The App is designed as an entertainment game for couples and may include romantic, playful, or relationship-themed prompts.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe that a child has provided personal information through the App, please contact us and we will take appropriate steps to remove such information where applicable.

11. USER CHOICES

You may control certain information and preferences directly inside the App, such as player names, language, music, sound, and game preferences.

You may reset or remove locally stored app data by clearing the App’s storage from your device settings or by uninstalling the App.

Advertising personalization may be managed through your device settings, Google settings, or available consent options depending on your region.

12. DATA RETENTION

Locally stored app data remains on your device until you clear the App’s storage or uninstall the App.

Data processed by third-party services such as Google AdMob, Firebase, and Google Play Billing is retained according to those services’ policies.

13. SECURITY

We use reasonable measures to keep the App stable and safe. However, no method of electronic storage or transmission over the internet is 100% secure.

14. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES

The App may use third-party services provided by Google, including Google AdMob, Firebase, and Google Play Billing. These services may collect and process data according to their own privacy policies.

